  "summary": "Capesize\nThe market delivered a volatile but constructive week overall, underpinned by a strong early rally and broadly supportive sentiment despite some mid-week consolidation. The Pacific led the initial charge, with C5 rates rising sharply through Tuesday as sustained miner activity and tightening tonnage pushed fixtures above $9.00. Momentum cooled slightly later in the week, before strengthening again into the close, with C5 ending back in the upper $9.00s.",
